<span id="freeTextContainer8253882497048471731">I read the wyrm lord for my SSR 2nd quarter project. It is a sequel to the first book and it is about Aidan Thomas a teen boy. He is back on Earth after his adventure in Alleble. When Aiden left the Realm, he saw a horrifying sight, his best friend Robby going on Paragor&apos;s side. Since Aiden can&apos;t go back he wants to find his friend and tell him the truth about King Eliam. Instead they&apos;re separated. He then he try&apos;s to get a hold of Robby so he can turn him to allegiance with the King. He meets a</span>
  <span id="freeText8253882497048471731" style="display:none">I read the wyrm lord for my SSR 2nd quarter project. It is a sequel to the first book and it is about Aidan Thomas a teen boy. He is back on Earth after his adventure in Alleble. When Aiden left the Realm, he saw a horrifying sight, his best friend Robby going on Paragor's side. Since Aiden can't go back he wants to find his friend and tell him the truth about King Eliam. Instead they're separated. He then he try's to get a hold of Robby so he can turn him to allegiance with the King. He meets a new friend at school, Antoinette, who is adopted and has a normal life. He then finds out that she is Gwenneâ€™s twin on Earth. Then they start to talk about his adventures. Then Antoinette starts wishing to go to Alleble. She gets the chance when a poem appears on the back of her copy of Allebleâ€™s scroll. Aidan asks her to find Robbie's glimpse in Alleble, and get him to follow the King. She leaves, and Aidan finds out he can to go to Maryland, where Robby lives. Antoinette is assigned to a mission to set in stone the alliance with Yewland, for they have been told of things Alleble has required of them, when in fact there were no such things. She has to find out what to do, either find Robby's glimpse for Aiden or complete the mission.<br /></span>
