  <span id="freeText11587074468043600224" style="display:none">Pros: This is the second book in 'The Door Within' trilogy. It introduces Antoinette, a new main character. Antoinette is confident and skilled. However, she has a lot to learn about obedience and trust.<br /><br />The first book in this series had sad moments, but was mostly filled with joyous and funny moments. 'The Rise of the Wyrm Lord' is more mature and serious.<br /> It showed the importance of doing the right thing. It also showed that trying to do the right thing, but in the wrong way, has consequences. Comprising in small ways can lead to to bigger compromises, with disastrous results.<br /><br />Overall a great second book in this trilogy. It has a cliffhanger ending. I am very much looking toward to read the concluding book, 'The Final Storm.'<br /><br />CONS: None. It was great!!!<br /><br />My rating: 5 out of 5 stars.</span>
